The Niger State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has extended the hands of fellowship to the leading opposition, Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state. The ruling party urged the main opposition to join it in putting the state on the path of development and growth. In a statement signed by the party’s publicity secretary, Alhaji Idris Abini in Minna, APC said with the determination of the governorship and National Assembly election petitions tribunal on Wednesday, it was time to shelve individual party differences for the benefit of the state. PDP can't win again in A/Ibom - Ekere Niger APC guber aspirant denies being ‘PDP stooge’ Nobody is intimidating APC - Commissioner OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY